wminc-code-macrolanguage:
Message shown for Incubator projects in languages that are defined as macrolanguages in ISO 639-3.

See also {{msg-mw|Wminc-code-collective}} and {{msg-mw|Wminc-code-retired}}

Parameters:
* $1 - (Unused) the language code (not used by default)
* $2 - the language name in English
* $3 - the translated language name from CLDR, if available (otherwise, English)
It is best '''not''' to change the link to the Wikipedia article about the language. The article about macrolanguage can be changed to point to a translated article.

Technical note: This message is not used in extension code, but is used by central templates on-wiki on the Wikimedia Incubator.
wminc-code-collective:
Message shown for Incubator projects in languages that are defined as collections of languages in ISO 639-3.

See also {{msg-mw|Wminc-code-macrolanguage}} and {{msg-mw|Wminc-code-retired}}

Parameters:
* $1 - the language code
* $2 - the language name in English
* $3 - the translated language name from CLDR, if available (otherwise, English) 
It is best '''not''' to change the link to the Wikipedia article about the language.

Technical note: This message is not used in extension code, but is used by central templates on-wiki on the Wikimedia Incubator.
wminc-custom-editnotice-2:
Edit notice shown when editing the User namespace.

Parameters:
* $1 – The wikicode for babel syntax, i.e. <nowiki>{{#babel:}}</nowiki>
* $2 – An example showing the babel syntax, i.e. <nowiki>{{#babel:fr-N|en-2}}</nowiki>

wminc-custom-featuredwikis-permanent: Shown on the Wikimedia Incubator main page above a list of test wikis that are unlikely to be approved (for policy reasons).
